  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Local infiltration analgesia is effective in total knee arthroplasty for postoperative pain
      management, but the efficacy of subcutaneous wound infiltration has not been evaluated. This
      study aims at evaluating the efficacy of subcutaneous wound infiltration in total knee
      arthroplasty in 16 patients undergoing bilateral knee arthroplasty.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
